  Locus:
    Page: 213
    Verse: 6
Tags:
  - Grief
---
We enjoy some gratification when our good friends die; for though their
death leaves us in sorrow, we have the consolatory assurance that they are
beyond the ills by which in this life even the best of men are broken down
or corrupted.
